### Test Authentication Flow

### 1. Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/TestAuth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "displayName": "Test User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "userName": "testuser",
  "phoneNumber": "1234567890",
  "password": "Test123!"
}

### 2. Login with the user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/TestAuth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "Test123!"
}

### 3. Test public endpoint (no auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/WeatherForecast/public

### 4. Test authenticated endpoint (copy token from login response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/TestAuth/test-auth
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 5. Test weather forecast authenticated endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/WeatherForecast/authenticated
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Variables
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7001
@authToken = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE 